      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "A race lacking quality with STERN REMINDER, who was very short in pre-post markets, coming out. FORTIANS (2) is a 17-start maiden who was just fair last time out over 1200m at Mudgee. Nicely drawn and on a quick back-up deserves another chance. ALLUSIVE INTENT (6) was handy enough but couldn't quite finish off at the end of 1000m at Dubbo last start. Lightly raced three-year-old having his first look at 1100m. Definite contender. NIGHTWALKER (4) registered an amazing 15th minor placing recently when third over 1300m at Dubbo. Can't recommend too highly after 33 unsuccessful trips to the races but must go in the exotics. KING LESONG (3) is struggling but in a race of this quality he is next best with the aid of the inside draw. ERION (1) is another struggling to make an impact but has placed here at this trip in the past.",
